news.title: China Evergrande winding-up hearing adjourned as it seeks new debt deal
news.para: The Hong Kong High Court agreed to further adjourn a hearing to wind up Evergrande to Dec. 4, with Justice Linda Chan saying the next hearing would be the last before a decision is made on liquidating the company.

news.title: China's property foreclosures up by a third so far in 2023
news.para: Property foreclosures in January-September rose to 584,000 units from 441,000 the same period last year, according to a survey by China Index Academy on Saturday, one of the country's largest independent real estate research firms.

news.title: SRG Housing Finance's profit up 20% in Q2 FY24
news.para: SRG Housing Finance's total income stood at Rs 31.19 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 36.26 per cent from Rs 22.89 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
